1. There were two groups being compared.
2. The visual analogue scale was used to measure pain severity.
3. The average pain severity score in group 1 was 5.33.
4. The standard deviation of the pain severity scores in group 1 was 1.22.
5. The average pain severity score in group 2 was 6.43.
6. The standard deviation of the pain severity scores in group 2 was 1.36.
7. The p-value comparing the pain severity scores between the two groups was 0.056.
